%N A114523 a(n) is the sign of the n-th Stieltjes constant.
%C A114523 In other words, a(n) is the sign of the coefficient of s^n in the expansion of zeta(1-s) where zeta is the Riemann zeta function. - _Jianing Song_, May 22 2026
%H A114523 Vaclav Kotesovec, <a href="/A114523/b114523.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A114523 Krzysztof Maślanka, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.07244">Asymptotic Properties of Stieltjes Constants</a>, arXiv:2210.07244 [math.NT], 2022.
%H A114523 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/StieltjesConstants.html">Stieltjes Constants</a>.
%H A114523 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stieltjes_constants">Stieltjes constants</a>.
%e A114523 0.57722, -0.072816, -0.0096904, 0.0020538, 0.0023254, ..., so the first terms are 1,-1,-1,1,1,...
%t A114523 a[n_] := Sign[StieltjesGamma[n]]; Array[a, 100, 0] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 22 2026 *)
%Y A114523 Cf. A114524, A394583 (indices of 1), A395455 (indices of -1).
